property.description:
Ballykillowen,  Laghey, South Donegal F94 KXC2

 

Traditional Farm House on 3.65 Acres

 

Requires Refurbishment

 

 

 

Situate adjoining the Laghey / Copany Road, 3 km from Laghey Village and 5km from Donegal Town.

 

Constructed in 1897 and extending to 98.42 sq m. The property may qualify with the new Vacant Property Refurbishment Grant. Surrounding by mature trees, the property which has been vacant for 20 years comprises -

 

Ground Floor. Living Room,  Lounge,  Kitchen, Pantry, Toilet;

First Floor 4 No. Bedrooms

*Traditional Stone Barn at rear

 

Excellent Grazing Field included at rear  

 

Sitting Room 3.64 m  x  3.61 m

Open fireplace

 

Living Room  3.68 m  x  3.46 m

Tiled Floor; “Wellstood” Solid fuel range

 

Kitchen 3.68 m  x  1.60 m

 

Pantry 

 

Toilet & Wash Basin 

 

First Floor.

 

Bedroom No.1 3.14 m  x  2.77 m fireplace

 

Bedroom No.2 3.65 m  x  3.35 m fireplace

 

Bedroom No.3 3.32 m  x  2.64 m

 

Bedroom No.4 3.67 m  x  2.03 m ( Ideal for conversion to Bathroom )

 

   

 

Septic Tank within Site

 

Electricity and Telephone - Currently cut off

 

Farm Lands Comprised in Folio DL 4482 and extending to 1.48 hectares ( 3.65 Acres )

 

To rear and and included in sale is an excellent grazing field extending to approximately 2.5 Acres. There is also a garden to front and rear of dwelling together with a stone barn.

 

        

 

  

 

 

 

 

 

Directions. From Laghey Village, travel over bridge opposite “7 Arches” Pub and continue for just 0.1 mile, turn right and continue for 1.8 miles; property for sale on left.
